cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use OpenEvalGate in research, evaluation practice, or production-readiness work, please cite the project and its maintainer."
title: "OpenEvalGate: Evidence-backed launch readiness for production AI assistants and agents"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Zhu
    given-names: Chenye
    alias: Charlie Zhu
version: 0.1.1
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/charliechenye/OpenEvalGate"
url: "https://chenyezhu.com/"
abstract: >-
  OpenEvalGate is a local-first GenAI governance and launch-readiness framework.
  It organizes golden evals, action-risk controls, human escalation evidence,
  hard blockers, operational ownership, observability, and rollback evidence
  into deterministic launch-readiness reports.
keywords:
  - generative AI
  - AI governance
  - AI agents
  - LLM evaluation
  - launch readiness
  - human escalation
  - trust preservation
